      "summary": "Three drone strikes hit AWS data centres in Bahrain and UAE — first time AI infrastructure targeted as a warfare objective. Chip concentration: HHI 0.59 (near monopoly). US debating tiered oversight of large Nvidia clusters. Acemoglu paper: AI shrinks knowledge commons by privatising problem-solving (no Stack Overflow trail). Azhar counter: AI democratises trapped knowledge. US productivity: 2.8% growth in 2025 (Q4–Q4), roughly 2x prior decade. Brynjolfsson: 'The old line \"we see AI everywhere but in the productivity statistics\" may need to be retired.' Critical caveat: 'These productivity numbers are still chatbot numbers. They mostly predate agents.' Goldman Sachs: AI added basically zero to US GDP in 2025; 80% of firms report no productivity gains. Azhar: measuring the wrong unit — institutions vs individuals. Donald Knuth let AI loose on an open combinatorics problem — it autonomously solved all odd cases; Knuth proved why it worked. Strong evidence for T03, T23, T25, and Article 49 Part 2.",
