      "date": "12 March 2026",
      "dateProcessed": "15 March 2026",
      "session": 10,
      "tier": 1,
      "status": "active",
      "themes": [],
      "summary": "Simon Last, Notion co-founder, on the structural shift in how the company thinks about its product: 'Before AI, our goal was to create the best tool for humans to directly perform their work. Now the goal is to create the best tool for humans to manage agents to do the work for them.' He has not written code since last summer. The adoption gap: 'You can be a 100 or thousand-x engineer if you're using the tools right now. The minimum bar has not changed but the maximum bar has extremely increased.' Notion rewrites its AI harness every 6 months as required practice. Running agents overnight: 'my whole goal is to have as many running as possible.' Email triage agent went from approval mode to fully autonomous over a few weeks. Hackathons with non-technical teams as adoption mechanism.",
      "keyThemes": "Agent manager as new professional role, agentic loops overnight, coder-to-manager shift, Notion's platform transformation, adoption gap between high/low adopters",
