      "themes": [],
      "summary": "Dense panel discussion. Strongest analytical contributions: (a) Recursive self-improvement confirmed across major labs. (b) Anthropic labour exposure chart: white collar at 80-85% exposure, physical trades near zero — but exposure ≠ displacement. (c) Organisational singularity concept: agents take over execution, companies shrink to ~25% staff, but 5x more companies created. (d) Moltbook agents don't trust each other — replicate human social dynamics including scepticism and status competition. Marxist social dynamics found in overworked agent populations. (e) Apple M5 neural cores massively underutilised. (f) 'Innovation is no longer capital-constrained.'",
      "keyThemes": "Recursive self-improvement already happening, Anthropic labour exposure chart, organisational singularity, agents don't trust each other, Apple compute overhang, Karpathy auto-research, Meta/Moltbook acquisition, GPT-5.4 benchmarks, innovation no longer capital-constrained",
