      "summary": "Deep dive on Claude Code skills architecture with strong enterprise relevance. Anthropic's Tariq mapped 28,000+ skills on ClawHub into nine categories. Two-category framework: capability uplift skills (depreciate as models improve) vs encoded preference skills (durable but only as good as fidelity to actual workflow). On code review: 'I don't think there's any chance that the paradigm of human review of all code gets out of 2026.' Skills convergence across entire stack: Notion, Codex, Claude Code, Cursor.",
