    "134": {
      "title": "#122: 2026-03-19-cognitive-revolution-zvi-s-mic-works-recursive-self-improvement-live-player",
      "source": "Cognitive Revolution",
      "host": "Nathan Labenz",
      "participants": "Zvi Mowshowitz (Don't Worry About the Vase)",
      "date": "19 March 2026",
      "dateProcessed": "20 March 2026",
      "session": 15,
      "tier": 1,
      "status": "active",
      "themes": [],
      "summary": "3+ hour conversation covering the full AI landscape. Five enterprise-relevant threads. (a) Lab competition: Only Big Three matter in the West. xAI disqualified by talent acquisition failure. Meta should license rather than build. US lead 'bigger and more robust than it looks.' DeepSeek V4 is the definitive test. (b) Google in danger — not model quality but scaffolding/integration/culture. Gemini models 'deeply psychologically screwed up and paranoid.' Recursive self-improvement gap compounds. (c) Model release fatigue: even GPT-5.4 got muted reception. Benchmarks 'kind of over.' (d) DoW pushing 'all lawful use' contract language across every government AI contract — meaning unlimited use, no refusal, no termination. 81% Manifold probability supply chain risk designation lifted within the year. (e) Personal productivity: flow-state preservation through context-switching elimination. Trust in dual-model verification — 'if both 5.4 and 4.6 agree, it's pretty trustworthy.' Validates Brightbeam's 'robust as a pair' methodology independently.",
      "keyThemes": "Lab competition thinning to Big Three, Google culture/scaffolding crisis, recursive self-improvement as key differentiator, model release fatigue, Anthropic-DoW conflict (all-lawful-use contracts), US-China AI gap more robust than it appears, DeepSeek V4 as litmus test, personal AI productivity practices, context-switching elimination, trust in AI verification",
      "postPotential": "very-high",
      "postPotentialReasoning": "",
      "_reconstructed": false,
      "url": "https://www.cognitiverevolution.ai/zvi-s-mic-works-recursive-self-improvement-live-player-analysis-anthropic-vs-dow-more/",
