    "138": {
      "title": "The Coolest Agents I've Built So Far",
      "source": "AI Daily Brief",
      "host": "Nathaniel Whittemore",
      "date": "14 March 2026",
      "dateProcessed": "2026-03-23",
      "session": 17,
      "tier": 1,
      "status": "active",
      "themes": [
        "T03",
        "T04",
        "T26",
        "T01"
      ],
      "summary": "Whittemore's inventory of 16 personally-built agents provides the most granular practitioner evidence in the corpus for how agentic workflows are actually being constructed and used. The episode surfaces three enterprise-relevant patterns: (a) the shift from one-off AI interactions to persistent, interconnected agent ecosystems with shared knowledge bases and automated update cycles; (b) the emergence of agent-mediated consulting — deploying voice agents across organisations to capture broader employee signal than traditional discovery, with a roadmap toward continuous rather than periodic assessment; (c) the gap between building agents and agents entering daily rotation, with several builds abandoned not for technical failure but for workflow-fit failure. The 'massive shift over the last three to four months' framing and the specific failure modes (OpenCLAW coder built but never used, Perplexity computer's generative search falling down) are more instructive than the successes.",
      "keyThemes": "Agentic ecosystem architecture, agent-mediated consulting discovery, workflow-fit as adoption filter, persistent vs one-shot agent design, vibe-coding as prototyping method",
      "postPotential": "medium-high",
      "postPotentialReasoning": "The practitioner detail — 16 agents built, several abandoned, specific failure modes documented — provides concrete evidence for the gap between agent building and agent adoption. The Holmes agent ecosystem (persistent individual profiling, automated weekly updates from a knowledge hub, Slack-native interaction) is the clearest single-practitioner example of what enterprise agentic deployment looks like when designed as a system rather than a tool. The 'Chucky' agent concept (agent as professional representative) surfaces a genuinely novel question about how AI builder competency gets demonstrated — relevant to hiring and talent assessment in AI-native organisations.",
      "_reconstructed": false,
      "filename": "2026-03-14-ai-daily-brief-the-coolest-agents-i-ve-built-so-far.md",
      "url": "https://podcasters.spotify.com/pod/show/nlw/episodes/The-Coolest-Agents-Ive-Built-So-Far-e3geoup"
    },
