      "summary": "A conversation with journalist Neil Shea about his book Frostlines — covering Arctic ecology, wolf encounters on Ellesmere Island, Inuit cultural hybridisation, caribou decline as identity crisis, and the Norse Greenland collapse. No direct AI or enterprise technology content. The episode's analytical contribution to the corpus is as a Tier 2 ambient source reinforcing T21's deliberate preservation problem: the Norse case (a civilisation that could observe better-adapted Inuit neighbours thriving but refused to adopt their methods, collapsing after nearly 500 years) and the Inuit hybridisation challenge (Marvin as conduit between nomadic past and Western present, communities navigating what to preserve and what to release) both illuminate the tension between identity preservation and adaptive survival — the same tension enterprises face when organisational identity ('we don't work that way') becomes the barrier to AI adoption.",
