      "summary": "Olivia Moore argues the AI market is structurally not winner-take-all: ChatGPT, Claude and Gemini are diverging into distinct market positions (mass-market, vertical enterprise, model-drop spikes), creating gaps where startups can build workflow-level and domain-specific products. The image generation market collapse — absorbed by platform chatbots — serves as the template for what happens to any feature-level AI company. The real opportunity is at the agent layer, which requires understanding organisational workflows rather than just generating text.",
      "keyThemes": "platform divergence, agent economy, startup defensibility, feature-vs-workflow companies, AI market structure",
