      "summary": "Whittemore maps the simultaneous convergence of ChatGPT (desktop super app merging chat + Codex + browser), Google AI Studio (adding vibe coding), and Lovable (expanding from code to general tasks). The pattern isn't feature bloat — it's recognition that code generation capability is the foundation layer for all knowledge work AI. Lovable's ARR jumped $300m to $400m in a single month, which undermines the 'spreading too thin' critique. Meanwhile, Apple's App Store crackdown on vibe coding apps reveals platform gatekeepers' first real friction with AI-native development.",
