      "summary": "Azhar decodes Jensen's GTC keynote through an economic lens. The headline: Nvidia's committed order backlog grew from $500bn to $1tn in one year — signed contracts for Blackwell and Vera Rubin chips through 2027. Jensen's claim: reasoning models create 10,000x compute demand per user, while usage increased 100x — a million-fold expansion in inference demand over roughly two years. Azhar maps his own team's adoption of OpenClaw agents — going from zero to four dedicated agents increasing company compute ownership by 50% in a month — as ground-level evidence of the demand curve Jensen describes.",
