      "summary": "Chris Power (Hadrian CEO) and Admiral Robert Goucher (USN submarine ZAR) describe rebuilding US submarine manufacturing capacity after decades of decline — a challenge where capital is available but skilled workers aren't. The episode surfaces a critical pattern for any precision industry: when the workforce bottleneck cannot be solved through hiring, software must multiply the productivity of available skilled workers. The defence context also demonstrates the acceleration possible when distributed multi-stakeholder accountability is replaced with single-person authority — Chris Power: 'three years ago it was incredibly difficult and now... is pretty fast.'",
