      "summary": "Whittemore tracks OpenAI's strategic consolidation: Sora shutdown to reclaim compute for the 'Spud' model, Altman narrowing his role to fundraising and infrastructure, the product division renamed 'AGI Deployment', and Codex positioned as the core commercial bet. The episode frames this against SpaceX/xAI's $75bn IPO filing and the Anthropic-Pentagon court case where Judge Rita Lynn called the government's conduct 'troubling'. Whittemore's central thesis: the labs have converged on 'work AGI' — discrete-task competence that breaks down when strung into longer workflows — as the only AGI definition that matters commercially, because even if the models qualify as AGI, diffusion into enterprise systems remains the unsolved problem.",
