      ],
      "summary": "Azeem Azhar describes adapting Andrej Karpathy's AutoResearch — a 600-line Python tool for iterative hypothesis-testing loops — to non-ML problems including headline optimisation and thesis refinement for his book. His extension, AutoWolf, adds an 'escape harness' to avoid local minima. The human role in this architecture shifts from executor to evaluator: 'your role moves from doing the work to judging the work.' The binding constraint throughout is measurement — if a goal cannot be reduced to a single scalar, the loop cannot run.",
      "keyThemes": "AutoResearch, agentic loops, scientific method democratisation, oracle/objective function design, human as judge, local minima in knowledge work, loop economy",
      "postPotential": "high",
      "postPotentialReasoning": "Azhar's practitioner account is unusually concrete — specific iteration counts, score progressions, and the memorable 'role moves from doing the work to judging the work' framing. Strong fit for Scott's enterprise audience as an accessible entry into agentic loop concepts."
    },
