          "content": "McKenzie describes the knowledge gap that enables compliance fraud to spread: a startup founder doing their first enterprise deal for $15,000 receives an email asking for SOC 2 compliance, Googles it, and buys a $10,000 certificate without understanding the difference between real and Potemkin compliance. 'That person might not realize that there is any intellectual effort involved at all here.' Editorial inference: given the viral chain-of-attestation design McKenzie describes, the enterprise diffusion gap cascades — enterprises relying on vendor SOC 2 attestations may inherit fraudulent attestations, which then propagate to their own vendors' requirements."
