          "content": "Turner Caldwell on why Mariana became an operator not just a SaaS vendor: 'software companies that sell to mining companies have a very, very hard time penetrating the sector because the issue is the rate of uptake of software and technology is actually gated by what would be the customers if you are a pure play SaaS company.' Solution: become both a software company and a mining company. The enterprise diffusion gap in physical-world industries is structural — the customer base lacks the measurement substrate to absorb software value without operational transformation."
