          "reasoning": "skills architecture is the implementation layer, flow-state preservation is a deployment consideration"
        },
        {
          "theme": "T10",
          "reasoning": "The Chucky agent — an agent that represents an agent builder's capabilities — surfaces a structural change in how technical competency gets demonstrated and evaluated. Traditional hiring signals (resume, cover letter, portfolio screenshots) break down for agentic engineering roles. This has direct implications for job displacement and the social contract: if the skill that matters most can't be demonstrated through existing credentialing mechanisms, both hiring and education systems need to adapt."
