          "content": "Intercom Apex beats frontier models for customer service: 2.8% higher resolution rate, 65% reduction in hallucinations, faster and cheaper. NLW framing: 'horizontal general-purpose models are actually over-serving the market for specific use cases.' Ben Afoji: 'Any vertical SaaS with enough labeled interaction data is sitting on an untapped fine-tuning asset. The infrastructure moat is eroding faster than most realize.' Over-serving dynamic means frontier models commanding premium prices may be structurally vulnerable in specific verticals."
