          "reasoning": "The 4K ceiling thesis directly affects AI investment economics. If most enterprise use cases hit a sufficiency ceiling well below the frontier, the massive CapEx being deployed on frontier model training may face diminishing returns for the majority of commercial applications. The investment case shifts from 'who has the best model' to 'who controls the platform where good-enough models run' — which is a fundamentally different capital allocation thesis. Apple's flat CapEx combined with growing AI revenue is the counter-case to the frontier labs' burn rates."
