    "T23": {
      "name": "Abundance Displacement - The Inversion of Value Under AI",
      "created": "Session 11",
      "lastUpdated": "Session 43",
      "documentCount": 26,
      "evidence": [
        {
          "session": 1,
          "source": "AI Daily Brief Pro-Worker AI (13 March)",
          "content": "Whittemore's 'opportunity AI vs efficiency AI' framing — clearest external articulation of Article 49's core thesis. Organisations stopping at efficiency lose long-term.",
          "url": "https://podcasts.apple.com/gb/podcast/pro-worker-ai/id1680633614?i=1000755168714"
        },
        {
          "session": 1,
          "source": "Helberg/a16z (18 March)",
          "content": "Secular growth acceleration frame — agrarian economies 0-1%, industrial 2-3%, AI era potentially 3-6%. US growth already broke 5%, productivity broke 5%.",
          "url": "https://a16z.simplecast.com/episodes/jacob-helberg-draft-6EvVv6rO"
        },
        {
          "session": 1,
          "source": "Moonshots Abundance Summit (17 March)",
          "content": "Organisational singularity — shrink to 25% staff, but 5x more companies created. Net employment potentially stable through proliferation rather than redistribution.",
          "url": "https://www.youtube.com/@PeterDiamandis/search?query=Meta%20Buys%20Moltbook%2C%20GPT%205.4%2C%20and%20Fruitfly%20Brain%20Upload%20%7C%20Moo"
        },
        {
          "session": 1,
          "source": "EV Newsletter/Azhar (19 March)",
          "content": "The 4K ceiling thesis. When local inference is good enough for most tasks, value shifts from model quality to platform control. The question flips from 'which model?' to 'whose device?' Apple positioned to capture abundance not through intelligence production but through the device layer.",
          "url": "https://www.exponentialview.co/p/why-i-changed-my-mind-about-apple"
        },
        {
          "session": 1,
          "source": "AI Daily Brief (19 March)",
          "content": "The freelancer 'exposed middle' is a micro-case of abundance displacement. AI simultaneously empowers freelancers (23% experiencing real benefits) and competes with them (17% experiencing real downsides). 'AI is both their tool and their competitor' — the displacement and the value creation are inseparable.",
          "url": "https://podcasters.spotify.com/pod/show/nlw/episodes/What-People-Really-Want-From-AI-e3gn965"
        },
        {
          "session": 1,
          "source": "Cognitive Revolution/Zvi (19 March)",
          "content": "Model release fatigue suggests intelligence abundance is already arriving. When even the AI-enthusiast community can't muster excitement for a new frontier model, the scarcity has shifted from capability to coordination.",
          "url": "https://www.cognitiverevolution.ai/zvi-s-mic-works-recursive-self-improvement-live-player-analysis-anthropic-vs-dow-more/"
        },
        {
          "session": 22,
          "source": "Exponential View Newsletter - Why I Changed My Mind About Apple (19 March 2026)",
          "content": "Apple as the value capture mechanism in an abundance regime. Azhar: 'Every third-party model ends up having to go through something Apple controls and that includes the App Store. They capture the value of those relationships even when they don't own the model.' Apple on track to surpass $1 billion in AI revenue in 2026. The displacement pattern: as model intelligence becomes abundant through distillation, value shifts from the intelligence layer to the platform/device layer. Apple's capture mechanism — App Store, privacy enclave, consumer trust, unified memory hardware — was built over two decades without being framed as an AI strategy. The abundance displacement here is structural: model providers compete on intelligence while Apple captures the interface rent.",
          "url": "https://www.exponentialview.co/p/why-i-changed-my-mind-about-apple"
        },
        {
          "session": 24,
          "source": "The a16z Show - AI Startups vs Big Chatbots (16 Mar 2026)",
          "content": "The image generation market collapse as abundance displacement: when creation becomes free, value inverts from the act of creating to the act of selecting, curating and integrating into workflows. Platform expansion accelerates this inversion.",
          "url": "https://a16z.simplecast.com/episodes/ai-startups-vs-big-chatbots-with-olivia-moore-h3P18Yyl"
        },
        {
          "session": 25,
          "source": "AI Daily Brief - A Guy Used AI to Cure His Dog's Cancer (16 Mar 2026)",
          "url": "https://podcasters.spotify.com/pod/show/nlw/episodes/A-Guy-Used-AI-to-Cure-His-Dogs-Cancer-e3ghqmv",
          "content": "ByteDance pauses global launch of C-Dance 2.0 due to copyright disputes with Hollywood studios. Disney, Warner Bros, Paramount, Netflix sent cease-and-desist notices. The guardrail engineering problem: blocking copyrighted content without frustrating legitimate use cases."
        },
        {
          "session": 34,
          "source": "Big Technology - Sorkin/Kantrowitz (18 Mar)",
          "content": "Kantrowitz presents the counter-thesis: Claude Code let him build workflow tools, which led him to pay for services he never would have otherwise — new economic activity created by AI capability. Sorkin's response: 'I become that much more productive. But I'm now not employing more people.' The wealth flows to model makers and those already at the top of food chains — they hire agents, not people.",
          "url": "https://www.podbean.com/ew/dir-wk4vx-2c0c8512"
        },
        {
          "session": 34,
          "source": "a16z Podcast - AI Just Gave You Superpowers (19 March 2026)",
          "url": "https://a16z.simplecast.com/episodes/ai-just-gave-you-superpowers-now-what-w1BZEEnu",
          "content": "The one-person billion-dollar startup made concrete: Lazarin — 'Is this not how that happens? What we're describing is exactly how that happens.' New framing of surplus: 'There's a new surplus. Learn to exploit it. That is the lesson for a young person.' Young person strategy: 'harness a huge swarm of computers and see like can I spend $5,000 of compute productively.' Augmented economy end state: 'lots of new jobs, lots of new things...anything that can be measured can be automated. So we'll converge at the cost of compute.' Agents described as '$200 a month employees.'"
        },
        {
          "session": 43,
          "source": "Moonshots - EP#242 - Elon's $5T Bet (26 March 2026)",
          "url": "https://www.youtube.com/@PeterDiamandis/search?query=Elon%27s+%245+Trillion+Bet%2C+the+End+of+Human+Drivers%2C+and+Chamat",
          "content": "Autonomous vehicles as abundance mechanism for real estate: Sem: 'land becomes abundant... real estate has been scarce, real estate becomes abundant.' Dave: '60% of the land area has parking spots in Los Angeles. That becomes gardens, greenland, parks.' Ride cost prediction: 10-30 cents per mile; 4-5x cheaper than owning a car. Fleet size collapse: 'even if you drop [car fleet] by 50% utility you basically collapse the need for half the car industry.' Island real estate 'becomes 10x, 100x more accessible.' AWG: cities may re-suburbanise — 'why invest in urban centre real estate if you can be effectively connected... basically a virtual subway from anywhere to anywhere.' Chamath thesis framed by Alex as 'bemoning the financial consequences of abundance' — scarcity-based valuations (moats, switching costs, scale advantages) all undermined simultaneously."
        }
      ],
