          "session": 34,
          "source": "AI Daily Brief - Rules Battle (23 Mar)",
          "content": "White House 7-point AI legislative framework: (1) protecting children and empowering parents, (2) safeguarding and strengthening American communities (data centre politics, electricity costs), (3) respecting intellectual property rights and supporting creators (training on copyrighted material — supports licensing frameworks), (4) preventing censorship and protecting free speech, (5) enabling innovation and ensuring American AI dominance, (6) educating Americans and developing an AI-ready workforce, (7) federal preemption of state regulation (longest section). Blackburn's 291-page bill competes. Cruz aligning with White House. Gottheimer (D): 'framework still has a long way to go.' Bannon's War Room: hostile — calls it 'profoundly anti-human.'",
