          "content": "Warner on Anthropic-Pentagon precedent: 'I've been trying to talk to all of the other tech companies and say, even if you are Anthropic's biggest competitor, you don't want this precedent set.' He argues the supply chain designation power shouldn't rest with a single individual (Hegseth). On AI regulation: he has a bipartisan bill with Josh Hawley. Criticises the White House framework as insufficient: Washington's legislative machinery can't match exponential technology change. Has a bipartisan bill with Josh Hawley (AI-Related Job Impacts Clarity Act) requiring quarterly reporting of AI-related job losses. Separately, Virginia is debating 'extracting somewhere between $500 million and $1 billion a year from the industry' in state-level data centre policy."
