          "url": "https://podcasters.spotify.com/pod/show/nlw/episodes/How-AI-Can-Help-Democracy-Work-Better-e3h3bkl",
          "content": "Andy Hall (Stanford) proposes a constitutional convention for the AI age — binding frameworks negotiated by companies, researchers, civil society and government. Distinguishes self-regulation from constitutional governance: 'The company writes it, interprets it, enforces it, and can rewrite it tomorrow. There's no separation of powers, no external enforcement, no mechanism by which anyone could check the company if it defected.' JPMorgan cited as parallel: already building AI system to vote $7 trillion in client assets; Hall argues public governance needs similar experiments. Three-layer framework: information layer (smarter voters), representation layer (advocate agents), governance layer (constitutional constraints on AI companies)."
