          "theme": "T03",
          "reasoning": "agentic systems and productivity — loops are the mechanism, skills architecture is the implementation"
        },
        {
          "theme": "T04",
          "reasoning": "agentic engineering — the skills required, building and maintaining skills is the core new engineering competency"
        },
        {
          "theme": "T05",
          "reasoning": "knowledge work commoditisation — loops commoditise the iteration cycle itself"
        },
        {
          "theme": "T01",
          "reasoning": "enterprise diffusion gap — most orgs nowhere near loop-aware"
        },
        {
          "theme": "T44",
          "reasoning": "Agentic loops are bounded by the measurability of their objective — T44 describes the design problem T26 depends on"
        }
      ]
